dmca.title: Individual Requests Google Cache Takedown of Previously Posted Image
dmca.body:
Dear Sir or Madam,

I recently discovered that an old image of my myself [sic] has apparantly made it on to googles [sic] image index. The image in question was originally a part of my personal webspace that I neglected to place a robots.txt file on. I would like to have it removed from googles [sic] image cache as I no longer have access to that webspace (it was an old dialup internet account that apparantly hasn't been deleted, but I have no access) - I will be contacting the ISP today to see if it can be removed.

http://home.iprimus.com.au/needlecracker/pic/mesmalldark.jpg 
http://home.iprimus.com.au/needlecracker/pic/wristwatch.jpg

The ISP that owns this webspace is: www.iprimus.com.au

You may contact me back at this email address: ([private]) for further information if you wish.

I swear, under penalty of perjury, that the information in the notification is accurate and that, for each image identified above, I either own the copyright or am authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed,

[Private]
